HEADWORD: Mugging
<hw>Mug"ging</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> from <er>mug</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <def>A robbery; a
taking of property by threatening (or performing) violence on the person
who is robbed. See <er>mug</er>, <pos>v.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> robbery, holdup, stickup</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

